nodes.title: Add ability to fetch restored glacier object
Upgrade embulk-util-config to 0.2.1, and bump itself up to v0.5.2-SNAPSHOT
Upgrade Gradle, dependency libraries, and bump itself up to v0.5.1-SNAPSHOT
Remove unnecessary items, .idea, classpath, and *.gem, from .gitignore
Remove ChangeLog, which is moved to Git annotated tags
Upload to Maven Central instead of Bintray
Update to Embulk v0.10.18, and not to depend on "embulk-core"
Fix the Maven artifact group settings
Add the Apache License 2.0 LICENSE file, and license boilerplates
Remove use of @ConfigInject by replacing with Exec.getBufferAllocator
Use the "org.embulk.embulk-plugins" Gradle plugin to build
Use java date formatting instead of Joda-Time
Use OpenJDK8 instead of Oracle JDK8 to fix CI failure
Enable aws-java-sdk-sts to use profile auth
Change `initial_retry_interval_millis` value from 30 sec to 2 sec
Disabled to set "PredefinedRetryPolicies.NO_RETRY_POLICY" to prevent "The target server failed to respond" failure
Revert log format change to show loaded file name
Restore "max connection" and "socket timeout" settings to prevent SocketTimeoutException
Update embulk version and use `java.util.Optional` and `java.util.function.Function`
Use file name output feature in Embulk core to show file name instead of logging
Don't allow to retry on some error and status codes
update getting single object by using path instead of boolean configuration
Allow the option to directly read path prefix object instead of listing all objects
Enhancement for retrying Riak S3 feature
Enable Riak CS jar artifact publishing
Fix: different resolved bucket's region when upgrading AWS SDK to 1.11.253
Upgrade AWS SDK to allow additional regions
add skip_glacier_object option to avoid loading a object stored at glacier
Throws ConfigEception if found no files
Set http_proxy.https option to true by default v2
Revert "Set http_proxy.https option to true by default"
Set http_proxy.https option to true by default
Upgrade gradle v3.2.1, Embulk v0.8.18, gradle bintray plugin v1.7
ExpiredToken should be treated as ConfigException
Use `DefaultAWSCredentialsProviderChain` to let aws-java-sdk to lookup available credentials automatically
add missing documents for incremental option
Added Duration unit to use sec, msec, usec, and min suffix in params
Add unit tests for min_task_size option
path_match_pattern uses Matcher#find() instead of matches()
Fix and refactor unit tests without mock
40x HTTP errors happen due to config exception
ConfigException if the specified bucket doesn't exist
Add sourceCompatibility and targetCompatibility to build.gradle
Add FileList unit which support limiting number of input files
Add support for multiple authentication mechanisms
Bump aws java sdk version. Fixes #15.
Enable logging of aws-sdk by including org.slf4j:jcl-over-slf4j
Set last_path to ConfigDiff in transaction()
